title: NFL | How former Buckeyes fared | Buckeye Xtra Sports
text:
Michael Bennett , DT, Jacksonville: Had two solo tackles in a 38-31 loss to Tampa Bay.
Brian Hartline , WR, Cleveland: Had one reception for 5 yards in a 33-30 overtime win at Baltimore.
A.J. Hawk , LB, Cincinnati: Had two solo tackles in a 27-24 overtime win over Seattle.
Daniel Herron , RB, Buffalo: Had nine carries for 28 yards in a 14-13 win over Tennessee.
>>  Dispatch  sports editor Ray Stein answers your questions about Buckeyes football during our weekly chat, 1 p.m. Thursday, dispatch.com/osuchat 
Malcolm Jenkins , FS, Philadelphia: Had six tackles (four solo, two for loss) in a 39-17 victory over New Orleans.
James Laurinaitis , LB, St. Louis: Had eight tackles (three solo) and one interception in a 24-10 loss to Green Bay.
Mike Nugent , PK, Cincinnati: Was 2 of 2 on field goals and 3 of 3 on extra points against Seattle.
Bradley Roby , CB, Denver: Had three tackles (two solo) in a 16-10 win over Oakland.
John Simon , LB, Houston: Had three tackles in a 27-20 loss to Indianapolis on Thursday.
Rod Smith , RB, Seattle: Had two carries for 5 yards in the loss to Cincinnati.
Donte Whitner , SS, Cleveland: Had nine total tackles (five solo) in the win over Baltimore.
Carlos Hyde , RB, San Francisco: Had 21 carries for 93 yards, including one touchdown, and one reception for 4 yards in a 30-27 loss to the New York Giants.
Johnathan Hankins , DT, Giants: Had three tackles (one solo) in the victory over the 49ers.
Others from central Ohio 
John Hughes , DE, Cleveland: Had one tackle against Baltimore.
Lance Moore , WR, Detroit: Had six catches for 55 yards and a touchdown in a 42-17 loss to Arizona.
Bradley McDougald , SS, Tampa Bay: Had three tackles (two solo) and one interception against Jacksonville.
